##  $ furnishingstatus: chr  "furnished" "furnished" "semi-furnished" "furnished" ...
# Convert binary categorical variables to 0/1
housing_data <- housing_data %>%
  mutate(mainroad = ifelse(mainroad == "yes", 1, 0),
         guestroom = ifelse(guestroom == "yes", 1, 0),
         basement = ifelse(basement == "yes", 1, 0),
         hotwaterheating = ifelse(hotwaterheating == "yes", 1, 0),
         airconditioning = ifelse(airconditioning == "yes", 1, 0),
         prefarea = ifelse(prefarea == "yes", 1, 0))

# Convert furnishingstatus to a factor with levels
housing_data$furnishingstatus <- as.factor(housing_data$furnishingstatus)

# Confirm data structure changes
str(housing_data)

Exploratory Data Analysis

# Scatter plot of price vs. square footage
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = area, y = price)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "Price vs. Area", x = "Area", y = "Price")

# Distribution of Price
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = price)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 30, fill = "blue", color = "black") +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Price", x = "Price", y = "Frequency")

# Distribution of Area
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = area)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 30, fill = "green", color = "black") +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Area", x = "Area", y = "Frequency")

# Distribution of Bedrooms
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = bedrooms)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 10, fill = "purple", color = "black") +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Bedrooms", x = "Bedrooms", y = "Frequency")

#Price and area relation
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = area, y = price)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "red", se = FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Price vs. Area", x = "Area", y = "Price")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

#Price and number of bedrooms
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = as.factor(bedrooms), y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot(fill = "orange") +
  labs(title = "Price vs. Bedrooms", x = "Number of Bedrooms", y = "Price")

#Price and number of bathrooms
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = as.factor(bathrooms), y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot(fill = "cyan") +
  labs(title = "Price vs. Bathrooms", x = "Number of Bathrooms", y = "Price")

#Price and furnishing status
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = furnishingstatus, y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot(fill = "purple") +
  labs(title = "Price vs. Furnishing Status", x = "Furnishing Status", y = "Price")

# Price vs Main Road
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = as.factor(mainroad), y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot(fill = "lightblue") +
  labs(title = "Price vs Main Road Presence", x = "Main Road (0 = No, 1 = Yes)", y = "Price")

# Price vs Guest Room
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = as.factor(guestroom), y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot(fill = "lightgreen") +
  labs(title = "Price vs Guest Room", x = "Guest Room (0 = No, 1 = Yes)", y = "Price")

# Price vs Basement
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = as.factor(basement), y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot(fill = "pink") +
  labs(title = "Price vs Basement", x = "Basement (0 = No, 1 = Yes)", y = "Price")

# Price vs Air Conditioning
ggplot(housing_data, aes(x = as.factor(airconditioning), y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot(fill = "lightcoral") +
  labs(title = "Price vs Air Conditioning", x = "Air Conditioning (0 = No, 1 = Yes)", y = "Price")

#correlation heatmap
cor_data <- cor(housing_data %>% select(price, area, bedrooms, bathrooms, stories, parking))
melted_cor <- melt(cor_data)

ggplot(data = melted_cor, aes(x = Var1, y = Var2, fill = value)) +
  geom_tile() +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "red", mid = "white", midpoint = 0, limit = c(-1,1)) +
  labs(title = "Heatmap of Correlations") +
  theme_minimal()
